            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Hmmmm, just not using the class in the other file _isn't_ enough, which makes sense...  I cannot think of a way to get Cython to include the class definition even though it is never used in a miminal reproducer. Maybe the `pymutex` isn't the problem at all, but rather that `PinnedMemoryPool` is pulled into `core.pyx` even though it is unused?\n\nI have a branch that reproduces it here: https://github.com/cupy/cupy/compare/main...seberg:cupy:pymutex-bug-repro including the generated `core.cpp` file that includes `PinnedMemoryPool` even though it is never used.\n\n(I don't think this is a problem in this particular instance. While somewhat public API, there is no reason to expose `PinnedMemoryPool` in this instance at all as there is no use to downstream.)\n\nEDIT: OK, no.  The class definition does get included also in my minimal tries. But the mutex doesn't create issues in them...",
